## Fork vs Template - What's the Difference?

| Feature | **Fork** | **Template** |
|---------|---------|------------|
| **What it does** | Creates a copy linked to original | Creates a clean copy (no link) |
| **Shows history** | Yes, shows all original commits | No, starts fresh |
| **Use case** | Contributing back to project | Starting your own version |
| **Best for** | Collaboration | Personal projects |

---

## Option A: FORK (If you want to contribute back)

**Fork** = Copy that stays connected to the original

```
Step 1: Go to https://github.com/Jen-Rad/link-checker-agent
Step 2: Click "Fork" button (top right)
Step 3: Creates your own copy: https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/link-checker-agent
Step 4: Clone it: git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/link-checker-agent.git
Step 5: Make changes, push back, create pull request
```

**Good for:** If you want to improve it and suggest changes back to me

---

## Option B: TEMPLATE (If you want your own separate version)

**Template** = Clean copy with NO connection to original

```
Step 1: Go to https://github.com/Jen-Rad/link-checker-agent
Step 2: Click "Use this template" button
Step 3: Name your new repo: "my-link-checker" or whatever
Step 4: Creates YOUR new repo: https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/my-link-checker
Step 5: Clone it: git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/my-link-checker.git
Step 6: Completely your own project - no connection to original
```

**Good for:** If you want your own version for other projects

---

## I Recommend: TEMPLATE âœ…

For your case, use **"Use this template"** because:
- âœ… You get your own separate project
- âœ… No connection to original (you can modify freely)
- âœ… Clean history (starts fresh)
- âœ… Perfect for copying to other projects
- âœ… Easy to use on multiple computers

---

## Step-by-Step: Use as Template

### On GitHub:
1. Go to: `https://github.com/Jen-Rad/link-checker-agent`
2. Click green **"Code"** button dropdown
3. Click **"Use this template"** (or look for template button)
4. Name it: `link-checker-backup` or `my-link-checker`
5. Click **"Create repository from template"**

### On Your Mac:
```bash
cd ~/Documents/new-project-folder
git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/my-link-checker.git
cd my-link-checker
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python link_checker_agent_enhanced.py
```

